'''Abelardo Aguilú Jr.''' (c. 1870 - c. 1940) was Mayor of [[Ponce, Puerto Rico]], from 1924 to 1925. Prior to that he was a shopkeeper in Ponce, selling groceries, liquor, and tobacco.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=mDwwAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA85 ''Commercial guide and business directory of Porto Rico.'' 1910. Pages 85, 91, and 94.] Retrieved 27 April 2010.</ref>
