'''Clarence Melville York''' (November 24, 1867 &ndash; June 20, 1906) was an American attorney who, in the 1890s, was one of the first law clerks to the justices of the [[Supreme Court of the United States]].
York was born in [[Vineland, New Jersey]] on November 24, 1867, and moved to [[Washington, D.C.]] in 1887.<ref name=GreenBag/>
In June 1889, York graduated with a [[Bachelor of law|LL.B.]] from [[National University School of Law]] (now the [[George Washington University Law School]]) in [[Washington, D.C.]].<ref>{{cite news|title=The National Law School, Graduates Who Will Receive Degrees Saturday Night|url=http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83045462/1889-06-05/ed-1/seq-8/#date1=1873&sort=date&date2=1925&searchType=advanced&language=&sequence=0&index=0&words=Clarence+M+York&proxdistance=5&state=District+of+Columbia&rows=20&ortext=&proxtext=&phrasetext=Clarence+M.+York&andtext=&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=1|accessdate=September 27, 2017|work=Evening Star (Washington, D.C.)|publisher=Library of Congress Historic Newspapers|date=June 5, 1889|page=8}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=National Law School Graduates|url=http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83045462/1889-06-10/ed-1/seq-8/#date1=1873&sort=date&date2=1925&searchType=advanced&language=&sequence=0&index=1&words=Clarence+M+York&proxdistance=5&state=District+of+Columbia&rows=20&ortext=&proxtext=&phrasetext=Clarence+M.+York&andtext=&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=1|accessdate=September 27, 2017|work=Evening star. (Washington, D.C.)|publisher=Library of Congress Historic Newspaper|date=June 10, 1889|page=8}}</ref> In 1890, he was a clerk at the [[General Land Office]]. From 1890 to 1896, York was a law clerk to Chief Justice [[Melville Fuller]]. He then clerked for Associate Justice [[Stephen Johnson Field]] from 1896 to 1897, before returning to clerk to Fuller from 1897 to 1905.<ref name=GreenBag>{{cite journal|last1=Peppers|first1=Todd C.|title=The Supreme Court and the Curse of the Gypsy|journal=Green Bag 2d|date=Winter 2010|volume=13|pages=173-186|url=http://www.greenbag.org/v13n2/v13n2_peppers.pdf|accessdate=September 27, 2017|format=PDF}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Peppers|first1=Todd C.|title=Courtiers of the Marble Palace: The Rise and Influence of the Supreme Court Law Clerk|date=2006|publisher=Stanford University Press|location=Stanford, CA|isbn=0804753822|page=49|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NxiMWr730EcC&pg=PA49&lpg=PA49&dq=%22thomas+h.+fitnam%22+melville+fuller&source=bl&ots=nuySib1rkx&sig=0UH5kXSy1rHuPmO-hnGRZ9XRd9I&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjc5YGuycXWAhUDyYMKHT5CDQcQ6AEIMTAC#v=onepage&q=%22thomas%20h.%20fitnam%22%20melville%20fuller&f=false|accessdate=September 27, 2017}}</ref> York is the longest-serving law clerk for the Court, his record of 17 years service equaled only by Frederick J. Haig.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Ward|first1=Artemus|last2=Weiden|first2=David L.|title=Sorcerers' Apprentices: 100 Years of Law Clerks at the United States Supreme Court|date=2007|publisher=NYU Press|location=New York, NY|isbn=0814794203|pages=31-32|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GCcUCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA31&lpg=PA31&dq=%22Clarence+M.+York%22&source=bl&ots=4CZ_gxTwv3&sig=6dgAkdduq_IBX_NanEli7h2YOa4&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiqt_ee7sXWAhUU0mMKHVzECqgQ6AEIRzAI#v=onepage&q=%22Clarence%20M.%20York%22&f=false|accessdate=September 27, 2017}}</ref>
On June 20, 1906, York died in Washington, D.C..<ref>{{cite news|title=Meets Tragic Death, Clarence York's Fatal Fall from Hospital Window|url=http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83045462/1906-06-20/ed-1/seq-2/#date1=1873&sort=date&date2=1925&searchType=advanced&language=&sequence=0&index=4&words=Clarence+M+York&proxdistance=5&state=District+of+Columbia&rows=20&ortext=&proxtext=&phrasetext=Clarence+M.+York&andtext=&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=1|accessdate=September 27, 2017|work=Evening Star (Washington, D.C.)|publisher=Library of Congress Historic Newspaper|date=June 20, 1906|page=2}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Was Due to Accident, Coroner's Certificate in Death of Clarence York|url=http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn83045462/1906-06-21/ed-1/seq-12/#date1=1873&sort=date&date2=1925&searchType=advanced&language=&sequence=0&index=6&words=Clarence+M+York&proxdistance=5&state=District+of+Columbia&rows=20&ortext=&proxtext=&phrasetext=Clarence+M.+York&andtext=&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=1|accessdate=September 27, 2017|work=Evening Star (Washington, D.C.)|publisher=Library of Congress Historic Newspapers|date=June 21, 1906|page=12}}</ref>
